FBIS4-41780 "drsov124_h_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 25 Jun 1994 Moldova Says Army `Not Interested' in Resolving Conflict Says Army `Not Interested' in Resolving Conflict PM2706144594 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jun 94 p 2 PM2706144594 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [INTERFAX report: "The 14th Army Likes It in the Dniester Region"] [Text] At a news conference held in Moscow Igor Smirnov, president of the self-proclaimed Dniester Moldavian [Moldovan] Republic [DMR], declared that "individuals in the 14th Army are not interested in resolving the conflict" between Moldavia [Moldova] and the DMR. He based his opinion on the argument that the wages of a 14th Army officer stand at 300,000 Russian rubles, i.e. 1.5 million former Soviet rubles, which are the basic monetary unit in the DMR. Therefore, officers would not like to leave the Dniester region.
